    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Rear Cover - Removal - Flywheel</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26513.1.2" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Flywheel</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, do not reuse the flywheel bolts.</para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e3001401.3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06071.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Removing the transmission adapter ring bolts (stripped chassis)</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Stripped chassis applications only - In order to remove the flywheel assembly, remove all 12 bolts
                    (M10 x 35) securing the transmission adapter ring to the rear cover.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e3001402" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06010.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Removing the flywheel bolts (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 10 flywheel mounting bolts (M10 x 31 - CF) (M10 x 77 - stripped chassis) and discard
                bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The 10 flywheel mounting bolts are not reusable.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e3001403" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the flywheel (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove flywheel assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>(CF applications only) - To prevent engine damage, place the heel bar onto the head of a rear
                    cover bolt to remove the rear flywheel adapter. This will prevent cracking of the aluminum housing.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e3001404" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Removing the rear flywheel adapter (CF)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear cover bolt head locations (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Placement of the heel bar</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, carefully remove and store flywheel adapter or adapter hub. Damage to
                    the adapter sealing surface can result in a rear oil seal leak.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the head of the rear cover bolt for supporting the heel bar to remove the flywheel
                adapter.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the heel bar on the head of the rear cover bolt and the hook under the lip of the
                flywheel adapter.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Alternate between the two rear cover head bolts to pry off the flywheel adapter.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001405" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Flywheel adapter removed (CF)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dowel pin</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pin recess</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dust seal lip surface</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove flywheel adapter or adapter hub.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
